# Component Rules

## RSC vs Client boundary

Use React Server Components for data fetching. Add `'use client'` only for interactivity (event handlers, state, effects).

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — RSC fetches, passes data down
// app/page.tsx (server)
export default async function Page() {
  const result = await getStats();
  return <SummaryPanel stats={result} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD — client only for interaction
'use client';
export function FilterChips({ onChange }: Props) { ... }

// ❌ BAD — 'use client' on a data-loading component
'use client';
export default async function Page() { ... }
```

## Styling — CSS Modules + theme variables

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import styles from './SummaryPanel.module.css';
<div className={styles.panel}>...</div>
```

Theme colors via CSS variables defined in `app/globals.css`:
`--color-bg`, `--color-text`, `--color-accent`. Never hardcode hex in components.

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML: `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<th scope="col">`, `<button>`, `<nav>`.
- Sortable columns: `<th aria-sort="ascending">`.
- Keyboard navigation on table rows: `tabIndex={0}` + `onKeyDown` for Enter/Space.
- Contrast: WCAG AA (≥4.5:1 normal text, ≥3:1 large) in both light and dark themes.

## Responsive layout

Desktop: `<table>` layout. Mobile (`max-width: 640px`): card layout via CSS only — no JS breakpoint detection.

```css
/* components/RequirementsTable.module.css */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  thead { display: none; }
  tr { display: block; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
}
```
